#. <section class="sutta" id="sn2.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Nānātitthiyavagga"
msgstr "3. Various Sectarians"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Nānātitthiyasāvakasutta"
msgstr "30. The Disciples of Various Sectarians"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.66"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.152"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. <span class="evam">
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

#. </span>
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

#. VAR: sahali → sahalī (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
#. VAR: nīko → niṅko (bj, pts1) | niko (s1-3, km, pts2)
#. VAR: vegabbhari ca → veṭambarī ca (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.30:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sambahulā nānātitthiyasāvakā devaputtā asamo ca sahali ca nīko ca "
"ākoṭako ca vegabbhari ca māṇavagāmiyo ca abhikkantāya rattiyā "
"abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ veḷuvanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā "
"tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu."
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, several glorious gods lit up the entire Bamboo Grove. "
"They were Asama, Sahalī, Niṅka, Ākoṭaka, Vetambarī, and Māṇavagāmiya, and "
"all of them were disciples of various sectarian teachers. They went up to "
"the Buddha, bowed, and stood to one side."

msgctxt "sn2.30:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho asamo devaputto pūraṇaṃ kassapaṃ ārabbha bhagavato "
"santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Standing to one side, the god Asama recited this verse about Pūraṇa Kassapa "
"in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.1"
msgid "“Idha chinditamārite,"
msgstr "“In injuring and killing here,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.2"
msgid "Hatajānīsu kassapo;"
msgstr "in beating and extortion,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.3"
msgid "Na pāpaṃ samanupassati,"
msgstr "Kassapa saw no evil,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.4"
msgid "Puññaṃ vā pana attano;"
msgstr "nor any merit for oneself."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.5"
msgid "Sa ve vissāsamācikkhi,"
msgstr "What he taught should truly be trusted,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:2.6"
msgid "Satthā arahati mānanan”ti."
msgstr "he’s worthy of esteem as Teacher.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:3.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sahali devaputto makkhaliṃ gosālaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ "
"gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the god Sahalī recited this verse about Makkhali Gosala in the Buddha’s "
"presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.153"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.1"
msgid "“Tapojigucchāya susaṃvutatto,"
msgstr "“Through mortification in disgust of sin he became well restrained."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.2"
msgid "Vācaṃ pahāya kalahaṃ janena;"
msgstr "He gave up arguing with people."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.3"
msgid "Samosavajjā virato saccavādī,"
msgstr "Refraining from false speech, he spoke the truth."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Na hi nūna tādisaṃ karoti → naha nūna tādī pakaroti (bj, s1, s2, km, pts2) | nahi nūna tādī pakaroti (s3)
msgctxt "sn2.30:4.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna tādisaṃ karoti pāpan”ti."
msgstr "Surely such a man does no wrong!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
#. VAR: nāṭaputtaṃ → nātaputtaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn2.30:5.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho nīko devaputto nigaṇṭhaṃ nāṭaputtaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ "
"gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the god Niṅka recited this verse about Nigaṇṭha Nātaputta in the Buddha’"
"s presence:"

# Here BB’s discerning for nipaka doesn’t fit very well. See my note at AN 3.40
#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.1"
msgid "“Jegucchī nipako bhikkhu,"
msgstr "“Disgusted at sin, a self-disciplined mendicant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.2"
msgid "Cātuyāmasusaṃvuto;"
msgstr "well restrained in the four controls;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.3"
msgid "Diṭṭhaṃ sutañca ācikkhaṃ,"
msgstr "explaining what is seen and heard:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:6.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna kibbisī siyā”ti."
msgstr "surely he can be no sinner!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:7.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho ākoṭako devaputto nānātitthiye ārabbha bhagavato santike imaṃ "
"gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the god Ākoṭaka recited this verse about various sectarian teachers in "
"the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.1"
msgid "“Pakudhako kātiyāno nigaṇṭho,"
msgstr "“Pakudhaka, Kātiyāna, and Nigaṇṭha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.2"
msgid "Ye cāpime makkhalipūraṇāse;"
msgstr "as well as this Makkhali and Pūraṇa:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.3"
msgid "Gaṇassa satthāro sāmaññappattā,"
msgstr "Teachers of communities, attained ascetics,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:8.4"
msgid "Na hi nūna te sappurisehi dūre”ti."
msgstr "surely they weren’t far from truly good men!”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho vegabbhari devaputto ākoṭakaṃ devaputtaṃ gāthāya paccabhāsi:"
msgstr "Then the god Vetambarī replied to the god Ākoṭaka in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
#. VAR: Sahācaritena → sahāravenāpi (si, pts2) | saha racitena (s1-3) | sagāravenāpi (pts1)
#. VAR: sigālo → siṅgālo (mr)
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.1"
msgid "“Sahācaritena chavo sigālo,"
msgstr "“Though the wretched jackal howls along,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.2"
msgid "Na kotthuko sīhasamo kadāci;"
msgstr "it never equals the lion."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.3"
msgid "Naggo musāvādī gaṇassa satthā,"
msgstr "A naked liar with suspicious conduct,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:10.4"
msgid "Saṅkassarācāro na sataṃ sarikkho”ti."
msgstr "though they teach a community, doesn’t resemble the good.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.67"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.154"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:11.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māro pāpimā begabbhariṃ devaputtaṃ anvāvisitvā bhagavato santike "
"imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then Māra the Wicked took possession of the god Vetambarī and recited this "
"verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.1"
msgid "“Tapojigucchāya āyuttā,"
msgstr "“Those dedicated to mortification in disgust of sin,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.2"
msgid "pālayaṃ pavivekiyaṃ;"
msgstr "safeguarding their seclusion,"

# I’m not sure what this line means, and translate following comm.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.3"
msgid "Rūpe ca ye niviṭṭhāse,"
msgstr "attached to form,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.4"
msgid "devalokābhinandino;"
msgstr "they rejoice in the heavenly realm."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.5"
msgid "Te ve sammānusāsanti,"
msgstr "Indeed, those mortals give correct instructions"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:12.6"
msgid "paralokāya mātiyā”ti."
msgstr "regarding the next world.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:13.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā, māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāya "
"paccabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in "
"verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.1"
msgid "“Ye keci rūpā idha vā huraṃ vā,"
msgstr "“Whatever forms there are in this world or the world beyond,"

# One of the clearest references to the connection between the gods and the stars.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.2"
msgid "Ye cantalikkhasmiṃ pabhāsavaṇṇā;"
msgstr "and those of shining beauty in the sky,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.3"
msgid "Sabbeva te te namucippasatthā,"
msgstr "all of these you praise, Namuci,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:14.4"
msgid "Āmisaṃva macchānaṃ vadhāya khittā”ti."
msgstr "like bait tossed out for catching fish.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:15.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho māṇavagāmiyo devaputto bhagavantaṃ ārabbha bhagavato santike imā "
"gāthāyo abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Then the god Māṇavagāmiya recited this verse about the Buddha in his "
"presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.1"
msgid "“Vipulo rājagahīyānaṃ,"
msgstr "“Of all the mountains of Rājagaha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.2"
msgid "giri seṭṭho pavuccati;"
msgstr "Vipulo’s said to be the best."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.3"
msgid "Seto himavataṃ seṭṭho,"
msgstr "Seta is the best of the Himalayan peaks,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:16.4"
msgid "ādicco aghagāminaṃ."
msgstr "and the sun, of travelers in space."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.156"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.1"
msgid "Samuddo udadhinaṃ seṭṭho,"
msgstr "The ocean is the best of seas,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: nakkhattānaṃva candimā → nakkhattānañca candimā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.2"
msgid "nakkhattānaṃva candimā;"
msgstr "and the moon, of lights that shine at night."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.3"
msgid "Sadevakassa lokassa,"
msgstr "But in all the world with its gods,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.4"
msgid "buddho aggo pavuccatī”ti."
msgstr "the Buddha is declared foremost.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn2.30:17.5"
msgid "Nānātitthiyavaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.1"
msgid "Sivo khemo ca serī ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.2"
msgid "Ghaṭī jantu ca rohito;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.3"
msgid "Nando nandivisālo ca,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.4"
msgid "Susimo nānātitthiyena te dasāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn2.30:18.5"
msgid "Devaputtasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on Gods are complete."
